               <msContents>
                  <summary>A copy of the Commentary on the <title key="work_23661">Súra-i-Yúsuf</title>
                     (<title key="work_23661">Aḥsan al-Qiṣaṣ</title>). Browne states he had already discussed the
                     general characteristics of this work and this manuscript's
                     particular features in an earlier article (JRAS, April 1892,
                     pp. 261-8), and here adds a detailed concordance of chapter
                     names against a related manuscript in Baron Rosen's
                     collection.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_11-item1">
                     <author key="person_9878408" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9878408/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Bāb, ʻAlī Muḥammad
                           Shīrāzī, 1819-1850</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="person_9878408">the Bāb</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar" key="person_9878408">باب، ميرزا علي محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2661">Tafsīr sūrat Yūsuf</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_2661">Qayyūm
                        al-asmāʼ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_2661">تفسير سورة يوسف</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" type="alt" key="work_2661">قيوم الاسماء</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar"/>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" defective="true"/>
                     <note>Browne notes the title of the work plays on the numerical
                        equivalence (abjad) of "Qayyúm" and "Yúsuf" (both = 156),
                        hence "Súratu'l-Qayyúm" as an alternative name.</note>
                     <note>Browne gives a folio-by-folio concordance of chapter
                        (súra) names against those in Baron Rosen's manuscript of
                        the same work (Collections Scientifiques, iii, Manuscrits
                        Persans, p. 50), noting one chapter (the last) is missing
                        from his own list and that Baron Rosen's copy has 110
                        chapters rather than the expected 111. This concordance,
                        being essentially tabular, is not reproduced in full in
                        this draft.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/85"
                              >p.59</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl type="OC">See sub classmark <idno>BBC. 4</idno> in Browne's "Catalogue and
                           Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts (Continuation)", in Journal of the
                           Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain and Ireland (Oct., 1892):
                           637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="OC">See: ART. VII.-—Some Remarks on the BABI TEXTS edited by
